      <h2>Experience</h2>
      <div class="role-item">
        <h3>Senior Project Engineer — Spalding Sports Equipment</h3>
        <p class="muted">New product development, product evolution, and technical performance across backboard systems and inflates. Managed development calendars and cross-functional delivery under strict budgets and timelines.</p>
        <div class="list">
          <div>• Led facility closure and end-to-end relocation; retrofitted new site for three sports divisions (space, climate, utilities) with external vendors and internal stakeholders.</div>
          <div>• Built layouts in SolidWorks; managed schedules in Microsoft Project; delivered on budget with documented commissioning and QA/QC.</div>
          <div>• Directed CAD/BOM/prototyping and product analysis to improve reliability, manufacturability, and cost structure.</div>
          <div>• Facilitated ECNs and controlled documentation turnover (record drawings, manuals, asset info).</div>
          <div>• Coordinated supplier compliance on regulatory requirements and internal specs; supported IP expansion.</div>
          <div>• Managed data coordinator and outside resources (design firms, lab techs, CAD designers).</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="role-item">
        <h3>Maintenance Superintendent — Automotive CNC Production Facility</h3>
        <p class="muted">Operations leadership across 50+ CNC machining, quality processing, and assembly assets; reliability, safety, and performance focus.</p>
        <div class="list">
          <div>• Managed 12 technicians across 3 shifts; implemented team lead roles and increased staffing.</div>
          <div>• Established preventive/predictive maintenance practices; sustained uptime while maintaining budgets at or below targets.</div>
          <div>• Worked interdepartmentally and with vendors/contractors to deliver facility projects.</div>
          <div>• Launched industrial training via SKYTC/WKU and off-site paid programs.</div>
          <div>• Participated in Nemak North America Energy, Maintenance, and Safety Expert Teams.</div>
        </div>
